						               													<description>The quick-witted game for for quick-witted people!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pitwits challenges you to think fast, but think straight.  You all take a turn to read a set of five clues to the others, the clues get easier as more are read.  You simply shout out the answer when you think you know it; if correct all the others move down the board towards the pit and out of the game, if wrong then you move towards the pit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Movement is related to the number of clues which have been read before the answer is given - the more clues, the less movement - e.g. 1 clue = 5 spaces, 5 clues = 1 space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The last player left in the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
